Defendant Christopher M Martell in court.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant files the waiver of attorney form and wants to proceed to dispose of the case today.  The Defendant is sworn in and questioned by the Court.  The Court finds the Defendant is competent to represent himself and to proceed without counsel.   Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count  1.  Court finds defendant guilty.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

30 DAYS JAIL;

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR; (probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County)

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*50 Hours Community Service.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
DNA sample and surcharge: waived;
